This is the help page for the official Club Penguin Archives to-do list.

==General==
The to-do list compromises of two core templates; one for the header and another for the body of the template. The template used for the header is '''{{[[Template:ToDo1|ToDo1]]}}''' and it cannot be edited. The template used for the body of the template is '''{{[[Template:ToDo2|ToDo2]]}}''' and it has three values to be filled in. The first value is to be used to explain the objective at hand. The second value is to be used for the status of the featured user. The third and final value is used to feature the users working on the project.

Although is no set limit to how many <nowiki>{{ToDo2}}</nowiki> templates that can be placed after <nowiki>{{ToDo1}}</nowiki>, you must place '''|}''' after each set of <nowiki>{{ToDo2}}</nowiki> templates to prevent the template from breaking.

For example: 

<pre>
{{ToDo1}}
{{ToDo2
|Finish expanding all of this category.
|{{progress}}<br>{{progress}}<br>{{hold}}
|[[User:Example1|Example1]]<br>[[User:Example2|Example2]]<br>[[User:Example3|Example3]]
}}
{{ToDo2
|Expand the page to include more information.
|{{progress}}<br>{{hold}}<br>{{hold}}
|[[User:Example1|Example1]]<br>[[User:Example2|Example2]]<br>[[User:Example3|Example3]]
}}
|}
</pre>

The coding above will appear as the template below upon publishing or previewing.


{{ToDo1}}
{{ToDo2|Finish expanding all of this category.|{{progress}}<br>{{progress}}<br>{{hold}}|[[User:Example|Example1]]<br>[[User:Example|Example2]]<br>[[User:Example|Example3]]}}{{ToDo2|Expand the page to include more information.|{{progress}}<br>{{hold}}<br>{{hold}}|[[User:Example|Example1]]<br>[[User:Example|Example2]]<br>[[User:Example|Example3]]}}
|}

